  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some Facebook tips and hacks?",
  "response": "Here are some useful tips and hacks for using Facebook more effectively:\n\n### General Tips\n\n1. **Privacy Settings:**\n   - Review your privacy settings regularly to ensure you're comfortable with who can see your posts and profile information. Go to `Settings & Privacy` > `Privacy` to manage these settings.\n\n2. **Two-Factor Authentication:**\n   - Enable two-factor authentication for added security. Go to `Settings & Privacy` > `Security and Login` and turn on `Two-Factor Authentication`.\n\n3. **Save Posts for Later:**\n   - If you see a post you want to revisit, click the three dots at the top right of the post and select `Save post`. Access your saved posts by going to your profile and clicking `Saved`.\n\n4. **Use the 'Why Am I Seeing This Ad?' Feature:**\n   - Click on the three dots at the top right of any ad and select `Why am I seeing this?` to understand how your data is being used for targeted advertising.\n\n5. **Keyboard Shortcuts:**\n   - Use keyboard shortcuts to navigate Facebook quickly. For example, `J` and `K` let you scroll through posts, and `L` likes the current post.\n\n### Posting and Sharing\n\n6. **Schedule Posts:**\n   - Use the scheduling feature to post content at optimal times. When creating a post, click on the clock icon next to the `Post` button to schedule it.\n\n7. **Use the 'On This Day' Feature:**\n   - Access memories from past years by going to `Memories` in the left sidebar or by visiting `facebook.com/onthisday`.\n\n8. **Create Custom Friend Lists:**\n   - Organize your friends into custom lists to share posts with specific groups. Go to `Friends` > `Custom Lists` to create and manage these lists.\n\n9. **Pin Posts:**\n   - Pin important posts to the top of your profile or page. Click the three dots at the top right of the post and select `Pin to Profile` or `Pin to Top of Page`.\n\n### Messenger Hacks\n\n10. **Secret Conversations:**\n    - Use the secret conversations feature for end-to-end encrypted messages. Open a chat, click on the `i` icon, and select `Secret Conversation`.\n\n11. **Customize Chat Colors and Nicknames:**\n    - Customize your chat experience by setting unique colors and nicknames. Open a chat, click on the `i` icon, and select `Nicknames` or `Color`.\n\n12. **Quick Replies:**\n    - Use quick replies to respond to messages faster. Type `/` followed by a number (e.g., `/1`) to select a pre-written response.\n\n### Page Management\n\n13. **Insights and Analytics:**\n    - Regularly check your page's insights to understand your audience and optimize your content. Go to your page, click on `Insights` in the top navigation bar.\n\n14. **Use the 'Boost Post' Feature:**\n    - Boost important posts to reach a larger audience. Click `Boost Post` below the post you want to promote and follow the prompts.\n\n15. **Create Events:**\n    - Use the events feature to organize and promote gatherings. Click `Events` on the left sidebar of your page and select `Create Event`.\n\n### Productivity Hacks\n\n16. **Use Facebook as a To-Do List:**\n    - Create a private post or note listing your daily tasks and check them off as you complete them.\n\n17. **Group Collaboration:**\n    - Use Facebook groups for collaborative projects. Create a group, invite members, and use the `Files` and `Events` sections to manage your work.\n\n18. **Stay Updated with News:**\n    - Follow reputable news sources and use the `See First` feature to ensure their posts appear at the top of your news feed. Go to the news page, click `Following`, and select `See First`.\n\nBy incorporating these tips and hacks, you can enhance your experience on Facebook, boost your productivity, and better manage your privacy and security.",
